Must have HYDRUS installed on computer and allow all users Full control permissions.
The script 'shell_permissions.ps1' must be run in a windows power shell using 'run as administrator'.
To do so, first edit the shell_permissions script to the Bin directory of HYDRUS,
cd to the project directory of the runhydrus package, and run .\shell_permissions.ps1.
You can use: Get-Acl "C:\Path\To\HYDRUS\Bin" to check to see if the Access was changed
  to "Everyone Allow Full Control..."
